def solve():
    n = int(input())
    a = list(map(int, input().split()))

    b = a[:]
    b.sort()
    b = b[::-1]
    c = set(a)
    if a == b:
        if len(c) == len(a):
            print('NO')
        else:
            print('YES')
    else:
        print('YES')
    return

def main():
    t = 1
    t = int(input())
    for _ in range(t):
        solve()

    main()
